    "text": "(1)\nHouston Street (formerly Hammersley Street), south side, from West Street towards Greenwich Street. The Church of the Holy Comforter used to stand at No. 345-341, where the billboards now hide the vacant lot; it was taken down less than eight years before the date of this picture.\nJune 3, 1930.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n\n(2)\nThe same, a view all the way to Greenwich Street, three months later after the West to Washington Street block has been cleared, showing the east side of Washington Street, and, in the background, the new Standard Statistics Building under construction on the west side of Hudson Street, from King to Charlton Streets.\nSeptember 30, 1930.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n",
